Black amp Decker Corp announced Friday that a 
group of commercial banks has arranged 22 billion in financing 
for the companys 21 billion hostile takeover attempt for 
American Standard Inc 
The syndidate is composed of 19 domestic and foreign banks 
including Chase Manhattan Bank which earlier pledged 750 million 
of its own funds toward the deal the company said 
American Standard has vowed to fight Black amp Deckers 
65pershare bid saying it will consider a restructuring 
leveraged buyout or a friendly merger with another company The New 
Yorkbased manufacturer of plumbing heating and air conditioning 
equipment has urged its shareholders to reject the offer and has 
adopted a poison pill plan allowing shareholders to buy back 
their stock at half market value if the takeover succeeds 
Black amp Decker which currently owns just 100 shares of the 
company launched an effort Wednesday to oust American Standards 
board of directors Shareholders will be asked to vote their shares 
to remove 10 members of the companys board Black amp Decker said 
One of the objectives the suitor said was to remove the poison 
pill plan 
The Towson Mdbased tool and appliance maker also announced 
the expiration of a waiting period under the HartScottRodino 
Antitrust Improvements Act of 1976 The law required a 30day 
cooling off period to check for possible antitrust violations 
The screening process is over and that means there are no 
antitrust implications said Black amp Decker spokeswoman Barbara 
Lucas 
Mrs Lucas said the agreements with the banks are for permanent 
financing of the takeover Some of the 22 billion loan is for 
expenses related to the deal she said 
Black amp Decker launched its bid for American Standard on Jan 28 
